{"word":"ὀκέλλω","slug":"ὀκέλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀκέλλω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:κέλλω'><el>κέλλω</el></a>\n<p/>a nautical word, used,<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> of the seamen, <i>to run</i> [a ship] <i>aground</i> or <i>on shore</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> of the ship, <i>to run aground</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; so, <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}